# Panopticon

Panopticon is a debugger-based tracer for Python code: a way to
quickly visualize code execution conveniently. Traces generated are
[Catapult](https://chromium.googlesource.com/catapult/+/HEAD/tracing/README.md) compatible -- available at `chrome://tracing` if you're using
Chrome.

## Usage

### Run a command  directly
```
python3 -m panopticon -c "print('hello') -o print_hello.trace
```
### 
### Run a module
```
python3 -m panopticon -m custom_module -o module.trace
```

### Run a file
```
python3 -m panopticon custom_file.py -o file.trace
```

### Through code
```py
with panopticon.tracer.AsyncTracer() as at():
    call_code_to_trace
```

